title: Princess Diana's iconic dresses go up in Kensington Palace
text: show ad Power dressing in pastels: A collection of Princess Dianaâ€™s most iconic dresses is unveiled including a pink tuxedo-inspired gown and the baby blue frock she dazzled in as a debutante Princess Diana is an icon of 20th-century glamour and a new exhibition traces the evolution of her style Twenty-five different pieces have been selected and will go on public display at Kensington Palace this week Here we look at some of the most captivating gowns from the collection - and what they say about Diana Published: 12:46 GMT, 22 February 2017 | Updated: 13:35 GMT, 22 February 2017 13 shares
